  "commentary": "With SPX at 6589 sitting right between the massive negative gamma walls at 6590 (-39.2B) and 6585 (-33.2B), dealers are in heavy buy mode as they hedge short gamma positions, creating amplified buying pressure that's driving the current breakout momentum. The wall_break and gex_surge events confirm dealers just switched from selling into the 6605 positive gamma zone to aggressive buying as spot cracked below, and with total GEX at -157B, this amplifying regime will continue pushing price action in whatever direction it breaks. Watch 6605 as the critical flip level - any reclaim triggers dealer selling pressure, while a break below the 6580-6575 negative gamma cluster will unleash even more amplified buying.\n\nBottom line: dealers are amplifying the move higher right now, expect continued trending action until 6605.",
